 <H1>Disks</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Secondary storage device of choice. 
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Main advantage over tapes:  random access vs. sequential.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Data is stored and retrieved in units called disk blocks or pages.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Unlike RAM, time to retrieve a disk page varies depending upon location on disk.  
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Therefore, relative placement of pages on disk has major impact on DBMS performance!</UL></UL></P>

